.TH MINT-MECHANIC 1 "2026-07-19" "Mint Mechanic 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mint-mechanic \- the maintained tune-up tool for Linux Mint
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mint-mechanic
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Mint Mechanic
is a modern, Cinnamon-native successor to Stacer: a live system dashboard with
animated CPU, RAM and disk gauges plus a GPU dial, married to the action
features Mint does not ship.
.PP
It runs as the invoking user. Mutating actions (toggling services, cleaning,
uninstalling, installing missing packages) elevate per-action via
.BR pkexec (1);
the application itself is never run as root.
.SH VIEWS
.TP
.B Dashboard
Live analog gauges for CPU, RAM, disk and GPU, with network, load and uptime
readouts.
.TP
.B Services
Enable or disable systemd services with live status.
.TP
.B Startup
Toggle or remove per-user autostart entries.
.TP
.B Cleaner
Reclaim space: APT cache, orphaned packages, thumbnails, Trash and old logs.
.TP
.B Uninstaller
Search the manually-installed package set and remove or purge a selection.
.TP
.B Streamline
Export the manually-installed package set to a portable manifest, or import one
to diff against this machine and install what is missing.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/share/mint-mechanic/ltt
The application package.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR pkexec (1),
.BR systemctl (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Ron Craig (rclinux).
.SH BUGS
Report issues at https://github.com/rclinux/mint-mechanic
